It was observed that the application does not properly sanitize HTML content supplied within the email body. A recruiter user was able to inject arbitrary HTML markup into an email, which was subsequently rendered in emails sent to candidates. This allows modification of the email content beyond the intended formatting capabilities and may facilitate phishing, social engineering, content spoofing, or misleading communication with recipients.

Log in to the application as a recruiter user.
Navigate to the functionality used to send emails to candidates.
In the email body field, insert an HTML payload.
Submit the email to a candidate email address under the tester's control.
Open the received email.
Observe that the injected HTML is rendered within the email content.
Verify that the application does not sanitize or neutralize the injected HTML before sending the email.
